            </p>
         </fn>
         <fn id="d22e131a1310">
            <label>2</label>
            <p>
               <mixed-citation id="d22e138" publication-type="other">
Wage drift is the difference between award wages and actual wages.</mixed-citation>
            </p>
         </fn>
         <fn id="d22e145a1310">
            <label>3</label>
            <p>
               <mixed-citation id="d22e152" publication-type="other">
Although the Arbitration Commission has fully indexed wages, this has often been in the form of
plateau indexation, where the increase above the average wage is a lump sum equivalent to the gain
by the average worker.</mixed-citation>
            </p>
